'''Kovvada Atomic Power Project''' is a proposed 6,600&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]] [[nuclear power station]] in the state of [[Andhra Pradesh]], India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/ap-will-gain-most-from-kovvada-power-plant/article8799238.ece |title=‘A.P. will gain most from Kovvada power plant’ |work= [[The Hindu]] |first= K. Srinivasa |last= Rao|date= 2016-07-02 |accessdate=2017-02-16}}</ref> The project is planned over an area of  2067 acres. According to a GV Ramesh, the project director at NPCIL, close to 485 acres of land has already been handed over for the project by the Srikakulam district administration. The acquisition of the remaining 1582 acres of land is expected to be completed by October 2017. <ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/visakhapatnam/kovvada-nuclear-plant-land-acquisition-by-oct/articleshow/59814086.cms</ref>

